arXiv:2505.10580v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We study sharp asymptotics for the KPP equation under front-like initial data of types $\mathcal{O}(x^{k+1}e^{-\lambda_*x})$ and $\mathcal{O}(x^{ oldsymbol{
u}} e^{-\lambda x})$ as $x$ tends to infinity, with $0<\lambda<\lambda_*=\sqrt{f'(0)}$ and $k,  oldsymbol{
u}\in\mathbb{R}$. For the former type initial data, we prove that the position of the level sets is asymptotically $c_*t+ rac{k}{2\lambda_*}\ln t+\mathcal{O}(1)$ if $k>-3$, while $c_*t- rac{3}{2\lambda_*}\ln t+ rac{1}{\lambda_*}\ln\ln t+\mathcal{O}(1)$ if $k=-3$, where $c_*=2\lambda_*$. In contrast, we retrieve Bramson's $o(1)$ result if $k< -3$. Regarding the latter type initial data, we show that the level sets behave asymptotically like $ct+ rac{ oldsymbol{
u}}{\lambda}\ln t$ up to $\mathcal{O}(1)$ error in general setting, with $c=\lambda+f'(0)/\lambda$. Under the $\mathcal{O}(1)$ results, the "convergence along level sets" results are also demonstrated. Moreover, we further refine the $\mathcal{O}(1)$ results above to the "convergence to a traveling wave" results provided that initial data decay like certain multiple of the above rates, which confirms, for general KPP nonlinearities, a conjecture in the probabilistic work of Berestycki-Brunet-Harris-Roberts (Commun. Math. Phys. 349, 857-893, 2017).
